figure.artwork:
Message Type - 1 byte Message Length - 4 bytes
/* One-Hot Response Codes */ RESP_INVALID 0 RESP_SUCCESS BIT(0) RESP_INVALID_LOGIN BIT(1) RESP_INVALID_CHANNEL_NAME BIT(2) RESP_NOT_IN_CHANNEL BIT(3) RESP_ALREADY_IN_CHANNEL BIT(4) RESP_SERVER_HAS_NO_CHANNELS BIT(5) RESP_CANNOT_GET_USERS BIT(6) /* Don't add any defines greater than BIT(31) */ MAX_MSG_RESP_NUM BIT(31)
Message Response - 4 bytes Message Payload - Size dependent on payload

/* payload for LOGIN message type */
Source User - 16 bytes
Password    - 16 bytes

/* payload for JOIN message type */
Source User  - 16 bytes
Channel Name - 16 bytes

/* payload for LEAVE message type */
Source User  - 16 bytes
Channel Name - 16 bytes
